<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The controlling expression `0 == _MHD_IOV_MAX` is invariant when `_MHD_IOV_MAX` is a compile-time macro (it is guarded by `#ifdef _MHD_IOV_MAX`), so the condition is known at compile time and will always be true or false. This is not one of the permitted exceptions (infinite loops or a do-while false constant), so it violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 14.3. The `mhd_assert(0 < _MHD_IOV_MAX)` makes the runtime check redundant rather than removing the invariant controlling expression.
</scenario>

